il me and I do not know what to say that might ease her pain. pic.twitter.com/8Bumghwwb4 ANN7 (@ANN7tv) December 10, 2016 #GroundReport| #SfisoNcwaneFuneral| Band Member remembers the time he and fellow band members shared with #SfisoNcwane|Live #DSTV405 pic.twitter.com/rVE2kq72n8 ANN7 (@ANN7tv) December 10, 2016 Representing the Ncwane family Sfiso&#8217;s unlce Mduduzi Ncwane thanked all those who had been supporting the family since news of Sfiso&#8217;s death broke.#GroundReport| #SfisoNcwaneFuneral| Mdu Ncwane now speaking at the funeral|Live #DSTV405 pic.twitter.com/zEQIRYMoKN ANN7 (@ANN7tv) December 10, 2016 #SfisoNcwaneFuneral| Mdu Ncwane: I would like to thank everyone who has been with us as a family since we heard the news of Sfiso&#8217;s passing. ANN7 (@ANN7tv) December 10, 2016 Sfiso Ncwane died earlier in the week from suspected kidney failure.At the memorial services that took place in Durban and Johannesburg respectively, many described Ncwane as a person who loved his work and that was a true man of God.Sfiso Ncwane was buried at the Lala Kahle cemetery in Hillcrest.TNA Reporter